"It all depends on the type of wedding you're planning. For a no-fuss elopement without many (or any) vendors and no special location (or travel), there can be very little to no planning time at all, aside from the time it may take to acquire a marriage license.\u00a0<br/><br/>Meanwhile, some weddings can take literally years to plan (this is more common for elaborate, luxury weddings). That said, one year is a pretty standard time to plan (with 18 months on the longer end of average).\u00a0<br/><br/>It\u2019s also worth noting that many vendors opt not to book couples more than a year in advance, so you\u2019ll want to consider this when figuring out how far in advance to plan your wedding.<br/>photo: <a href=\"https://brunakitchenphotography.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Bruna Kitchen Photography</a>, as seen in <a href=\"https://greenweddingshoes.com/this-is-how-to-elope-in-big-sur-with-two-dresses-plenty-of-pampas-grass/\">this boho coastal wedding planned on the cliffs of Big Sur</a>", "inLanguage": "en-US"}, "inLanguage": "en-US"}, {"@type": "Question", "@id": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738261261439", "position": 2, "url": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738261261439", "name": "Can I plan a wedding in 3 months?", "answerCount": 1, "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Whether you can (or would want to) plan a wedding in 3 months depends on the type of event you\u2019re planning. If you\u2019re planning a micro to small wedding without too many vendors, minimal decor, and not too many moving parts, then you could absolutely plan a wedding in 3 months.\u00a0<br/><br/>However, even small weddings can require months of planning, so it\u2019s best to avoid forcing yourself to plan a wedding in 3 months or less if you can avoid it. It'll make all the steps in the wedding planning process that much easier and more enjoyable.<br/>photo: <a href=\"https://koko-photography.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Koko Photography</a>, as seen in <a href=\"https://greenweddingshoes.com/elopement-eiffel-tower-fairytale-dress/\">this romantic wedding inspo planned near the Eiffel Tower</a>", "inLanguage": "en-US"}, "inLanguage": "en-US"}, {"@type": "Question", "@id": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738261516622", "position": 3, "url": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738261516622", "name": "Is it easy to plan your own wedding?", "answerCount": 1, "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "It <em>can</em> be easy to plan your own wedding, but the answer here ultimately depends on your timeline and your personality type.\u00a0<br/><br/>If you\u2019re planning your large wedding within a short time window, planning your wedding would 100% be challenging. Meanwhile, if you\u2019re planning a moderately sized affair over a year or longer, it can be easy to plan your own wedding and cover all of our checklist steps with ease.\u00a0<br/><br/>Regarding personality type, you\u2019ll want to think about whether or not you\u2019re the type of person who can stick to strict deadlines, manage several tasks at once, and juggle outreach and communication with many vendors. Planning a wedding is essentially a project management job, and if you excel at that, it <em>can</em> be easy...but if not, it's best to call in the professionals.<br/><br/>That said, just because you <em>can</em> plan your own wedding doesn\u2019t necessarily mean you <em>should</em>. If you plan your own wedding, everything comes back to you, so if the flowers are late on the day of, or the caterer is running out of food, or anything goes wrong on the day of, it's something you'll need to deal with personally. However, if you work with a planner, all those issues will be addressed by them while you have the time of your life at your own wedding!<br/><br/>photo: <a href=\"https://www.brookemillerphotography.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Brooke Miller Photography</a>, as seen in <a href=\"https://greenweddingshoes.com/sentimental-backyard-wedding-vintage-cars/\">this backyard Georgia wedding planned with classic car touches</a>", "inLanguage": "en-US"}, "inLanguage": "en-US"}, {"@type": "Question", "@id": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738261642997", "position": 4, "url": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738261642997", "name": "Do I need a wedding planner?", "answerCount": 1, "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Generally speaking, we\u2019re big advocates for hiring a wedding planner, but there are some exceptions where having one on your vendor team may not be necessary.\u00a0<br/><br/>You may need a wedding planner in the following scenarios:<br/>- <strong>To Work With Certain Vendors -</strong> Some wedding vendors only work with clients with a dedicated wedding planner (this is often the case with luxury wedding photographers and other top-tier vendors).<br/><br/>- <strong>For Large Events -</strong> The more moving parts in your wedding day, the more essential a wedding planner will be. They can help you find your other vendors and will communicate the timeline and plan for the day so you don\u2019t have to.<br/><br/>- <strong>For a Low Stress Experience -</strong> Wedding planners can do a ton for you, including helping you manage your wedding budget, coordinating meetings with vendors, providing a recommended vendor list, helping gather loved ones for important moments on the big day (like family photos!), and so much more. Without them, you\u2019d be planning and managing all that yourself, which is a lot to do before and during your wedding day.<br/>photo: <a href=\"https://atmosphere.pt/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Atmosphere Photography</a>, as seen in <a href=\"https://greenweddingshoes.com/bridgerton-inspired-elopement-palace-in-portugal/\">this Bridgerton-inspired wedding planned at a Portuguese palace</a><br/><br/>You may not need a wedding planner in the following scenarios:<br/>- <strong>For Smaller Events</strong> - If you\u2019re eloping, your photographer will provide a lot of the planning services, like creating your timeline and helping you identify and navigate the booking process for your location. They also typically have a list of preferred vendors they can share with you.<br/><br/>- <strong>If You Just Need Help The Day-Of</strong> - If you can plan everything before the wedding day and solely need someone to help with the day-of logistics and keep things running smoothly, a day-of coordinator is a great alternative.<br/><br/>Whether you hire a wedding planner to plan your wedding or not, we recommend having a <a href=\"https://greenweddingshoes.com/best-wedding-planner-books/\">dedicated planner notebook</a> to keep track of everything as you go.", "inLanguage": "en-US"}, "inLanguage": "en-US"}, {"@type": "Question", "@id": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738262283403", "position": 5, "url": "https://greenweddingshoes.com/how-to-plan-a-wedding/#faq-question-1738262283403", "name": "How do you start planning a wedding?", "answerCount": 1, "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "It\u2019s easy to get overwhelmed in the whole process of how to plan a wedding.
